      <resourceName lang="en">German Pronunciation Rules Set - PHONRUL 9.0</resourceName>
      <resourceName lang="fr">Ensemble de r&#232;gles de prononciation de l'allemand - PHONRUL 9.0</resourceName>
      <description lang="en">PHONRUL is a collection of computer-readable underspecifying pronunciation rules of standard German. This set describes the most common known effects in German pronunciation if deviating from the so-called canonic or citation form of words. The knowledge of this rule set was derived from empirical analysis of speech corpora as well as from a multitude of publications about German phonetics. The set does not contain any dialect-specific rules, however the line between Standard German and dialects is indistinct. Presently, this rule set is used at the University of Munich to aid automatic segmentation and labelling of unknown speech utterances.The rule set, in its present form, consists of approximately 1,500 complex rules which expand to 5,546 simple replacement rules. The rule set was designed for extended German SAM-PA, but can be translated into other alphabets (e.g. Worldbet, IPA) without much effort.</description>
      <description lang="fr">PHONRUL est un ensemble de r&#232;gles de prononciation de l'allemand "standard". Cet ensemble d&#233;crit les effets les plus connus de la prononciation allemande lorsqu'elle est d&#233;vi&#233;e de sa forme dite canonique ou locutive. Cet ensemble de r&#232;gles provient d'une analyse empirique de corpus oraux, ainsi que d'un nombre tr&#232;s important de publications sur la phon&#233;tique allemande. L'ensemble ne contient pas de r&#232;gles sp&#233;cifiques aux dialectes, m&#234;me si la fronti&#232;re entre l'allemand standard et les dialectes est peu distincte. Actuellement, cet ensemble de r&#232;gles est utilis&#233; &#224; l'Universit&#233; de Munich pour l'aide &#224; la segmentation automatique et &#224; l'&#233;tiquetage d'occurrences de parole, non connues.PHONRUL, dans sa forme actuelle, comprend environ 1 500 r&#232;gles complexes qui permettent d'obtenir environ 5 546 r&#232;gles simples de remplacement. L'ensemble de r&#232;gles est con&#231;u pour l'alphabet SAM-PA tel qu'&#233;tendu &#224; l'allemand, mais peut &#234;tre facilement traduit en d'autres alphabets tels que Worldbet et IPA.</description>
